In order to install **Mini-NDN**, follow the steps below. All of them are required!

### What equipment will I need ?

Basically, you'll need a laptop/desktop with a recent Linux distro (Ubuntu, Fedora). We recommend Ubuntu. For this guide, the _Ubuntu 12.04 LTS_ was used. Also, note that you'll need administrative privileges in order to download and install extra packages and also to execute **Mini-NDNx**.

### Installing Mini-NDN Prerequisites

Each node in **Mini-NDN** will run the official implementations of NFD and NLSR.

Please follow the installation instructions for NFD and NLSR:

* [NFD Installation](https://github.com/named-data/NFD/blob/master/docs/INSTALL.rst)
* [NLSR Installation](http://named-data.net/doc/NLSR/current/INSTALL.html)

### Downloading and installing **Mini-NDN**

First, retrieve the source code of **Mini-NDNx**.
Go to your home directory and use the following command:

`git clone https://github.com/agawande/mn-ndn`

As result, there will be a directory named 'mn-ndn' in your home directory which contains the source code.

Still in your home directory, use the utility install script with the _-fnv_ options:

`sudo ./mn-ndn/util/install.sh -fnv`

Pre-requisite packages will be downloaded and installed during the process.
